Some refactoring tests failed in N20060221-0010 on Mac.  These assertion failures in the log seem to be the culprit:

 org.eclipse.core.runtime.AssertionFailedException: assertion failed: 
 at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:107)
 at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:93)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.watson.ElementTree.openElementData(ElementTree.java:640)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.Workspace.getResourceInfo(Workspace.java:1178)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.Resource.getResourceInfo(Resource.java:1051)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.NatureManager$1.run(NatureManager.java:141)
 at org.eclipse.core.runtime.SafeRunner.run(SafeRunner.java:37)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.NatureManager.configureNature(NatureManager.java:155)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.NatureManager.configureNatures(NatureManager.java:200)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.Project.basicSetDescription(Project.java:64)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.Project.setDescription(Project.java:987)
 at org.eclipse.core.internal.resources.Project.setDescription(Project.java:1015)
 at org.eclipse.jdt.testplugin.JavaProjectHelper.addNatureToProject(JavaProjectHelper.java:689)
 at org.eclipse.jdt.testplugin.JavaProjectHelper.createJavaProject(JavaProjectHelper.java:135)
 at org.eclipse.jdt.ui.tests.refactoring.RefactoringTestSetup.setUp(RefactoringTestSetup.java:67)

See also bug 95089.

AFAICS, this exception happened after the 'endRule without matching beginRule' from bug 95089.

The exception from bug 95089 happens during PullUpTests#test13(..).
The exception here seems to come from the first test of PushDownTests, which is run after the PullUpTests suite.

I believe this is a side-effect of the bad state after the error in bug 95089.

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 95089 ***
